          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">A shift in Syria</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The reported fall of Bashar al-Assad’s regime marks a <a href="https://abcnews.go.com/International/syrian-rebels-claimed-4-cities-24-hours-now/story?id=116562929" target=="_blank">dramatic shift</a> in the Syrian Civil War. After a lightning advance by rebel forces, particularly Hayat Tahrir al-Sham (HTS), Assad’s government appears to have collapsed. HTS declared Damascus free, claiming Assad had fled the capital and the country. Russian authorities confirmed Assad’s decision to step down and leave Syria. He is being <a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/russia-asylum-bashar-assad-kremlin-syria-bloody-civil-war-middle-east-moscow/" target=="_blank">granted</a> asylum in Russia. This marks the end of Bashar al-Assad's 24-year rule, which began in 2000 after his father, Hafez al-Assad, came to power in 1971.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Assad's regime relied heavily on foreign support from Russia and Iran, but reports indicate that both countries have reduced their involvement. The Syrian Civil War, which started in 2011, has resulted in immense human suffering, with hundreds of thousands dead and millions displaced. The rebel push has been rapid, with major cities like Homs, Daraa, and Sweida falling, and the Syrian military has reportedly surrendered. The Syrian refugees have started to move towards their homeland.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
