        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>A US appeals court upheld a law banning TikTok</strong> unless its Chinese parent, ByteDance, sells its stake. The court ruled that national security outweighed concerns about free speech. Officials fear China could misuse user data or manipulate content. The law takes effect on Jan. 19 (<a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/amp/news/tiktok-ban-appeals-court-congress/" target=="_blank">read more</a>).</p>
             <p style="
