              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Coffee prices have surged to a 47-year high</strong>, with Arabica futures reaching $3.36 per pound. This <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/video/why-coffee-prices-trading-near-154921955.html" target=="_blank">increase</a> is mainly due to extreme weather, including droughts and heavy rains in Brazil and Vietnam, which have disrupted coffee production and harvests, creating supply concerns.</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
