              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Trump recently dismissed the possibility of removing Fed Chair Jerome Powell</strong> but claimed Powell would step down if ordered. Trump has criticized Powell over interest rate decisions and opposed Fed independence. Powell reaffirmed the Fed’s statutory independence despite political pressure (<a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/08/business/trump-fed-chair-jerome-powell/index.html" target=="_blank">read more</a>).</p>
            <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              border-left: 3px solid #4c305f;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
            "><strong>Hong Kong’s $2.7 billion infrastructure bond offering was undersubscribed</strong>, raising <a href="https://www.scmp.com/business/article/3289759/hong-kong-us27-billion-infrastructure-bond-offering-undersubscribed?module=top_story&pgtype=section" target=="_blank">$2.28 billion</a> as investors favored IPOs and stable-return projects. The government will announce the allocation results on December 13, and the bonds will be released on December 17.</p>
